# grazel-app.glade — gryth's workspace app, declared as DATA (GDL-037/038).
#
# This file is LOADED, never compiled: a node registers each declaration as an
# ordinary home-share record under the registrant's chain (byte-identical to
# what dynamic configuration writes), and each ACL seed COMPILES TO a
# CapabilityGrant record at registration. The fold stays the only runtime
# authority — a runtime revocation beats a re-registered seed, always.
# Base glade knows nothing in this file; grazel is just the first contributor.
#
# DUAL-MAINTENANCE NOTE (P1.S3): this file is kept BYTE-IDENTICAL in two homes —
# grazel/apps/grazel-app.glade (grazel owns its declaration) and
# glade/apps/grazel-app.glade (the demo's copy). Edit both together until a
# single shared source is factored out (future dedup item).
#
# Executable spec: ggg-viz s-app-register.
glade-app v0
app grazel

# binding <glade_id> <shape> <authority> <zone> <retention>
# App-static surfaces: no share/key here — the ServeClaim selects the node,
# the mount fills domain/zone/key (GladeDeclSurface.md).
binding ws.tree   value share commons latest
binding ws.files  log   share commons from-cursor
binding ws.diff   log   share private from-cursor
binding term.log  log   share commons windowed

# Supplier surfaces grazel composes (P1.S3): glade-gwz's long-op output stream,
# and glade-chat's group-keyed message log + group-list value. Pre-declared so
# the surfaces exist node-side regardless of a running supplier host — the chat
# supplier is TS/in-process in the UI host (grazel does NOT run it in P1), so its
# surfaces are declared here rather than by a grazel-spawned process.
binding gwz.output  log   share commons from-cursor
binding chat.msgs   log   share commons from-cursor
binding chat.groups value share commons latest

# service <name> <exchange-glade-id>
# The authority provider grazel attaches, and the DIRECTED surface it answers.
# Exchanges never fan out: only the claim-holding node's provider replies.
service grazel gwz.ops

# seed <principal> <share> <verb[,verb...]>
# Bootstrap shortcuts, not a parallel ACL system: compiled to CapabilityGrant
# records at registration; ordinary fold rules (revocation wins) from then on.
seed owner grazel read.*
seed owner grazel gwz.*

# workspace <share> <name>
# The workspace share this app serves from (audit F1): the node LOADING this
# file registers the WorkspaceEntry with itself as eligible host and mints +
# renews the ServeClaim while serving. Deployment picks the loader; the file
# stays data. Required for `(ws-razel, gwz.ops)` to route to the composed
# glade-gwz supplier.
workspace ws-razel razel
